law.text:
The State Superintendent, in collaboration with the Secretary of Business and Economic Development, may:
Provide direction and support for the conduct of research on advanced educational technologies;
Provide support for long-term comprehensive educational applications of advanced high performance computer and communication technologies and video technologies in support of the core subjects of the National Education Goals;
Ensure that high performance computing and telecommunications networks (or information highways) are developed with consideration to the needs of elementary and secondary education to facilitate educational uses, to provide access to classrooms and libraries in elementary and secondary schools, and to improve student learning; and
Assess the effectiveness of technology in education programs.
